The [[2020 United States census]] reported that Fellows had a population of 52. The population density was {{convert|74.8|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Fellows was 46 (88%) [[White Americans|White]], 3 (6%) [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], and 3 (6%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race was 1 person (2%).<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=Fellows CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0623812 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 20, 2025}}</ref>

The whole population lived in households. There were 23 households, out of which 8 (35%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 9 (39%) were married-couple households, 3 (13%) were [[cohabitation|cohabiting]] couple households, 9 (39%) had a female householder with no partner present, and 2 (9%) had a male householder with no partner present. 8 households (35%) were one person, and 6 (26%) were one person aged 65 or older. The average household size was 2.26.<ref name=DP1/> There were 15 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (65% of all households).<ref>{{cite web |title=Fellows CDP, California; P16: Household Type - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDHC2020.P16?g=1600000US0623812 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 20, 2025}}</ref>

The age distribution was 9 people (17%) under the age of 18, 7 people (13%) aged 18 to 24, 2 people (4%) aged 25 to 44, 20 people (38%) aged 45 to 64, and 14 people (27%) who were 65{{nbsp}}years of age or older. The median age was 57.5{{nbsp}}years. There were 26 males and 26 females.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 24 housing units at an average density of {{convert|34.5|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 23 (96%) were occupied. Of these, 16 (70%) were owner-occupied, and 7 (30%) were occupied by renters.<ref name=DP1/>

===2010===
At the [[2010 United States Census|2010 census]] Fellows had a population of 106. The population density was {{convert|161.5|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Fellows was 94 (88.7%) White, 1 (0.9%) African American, 5 (4.7%) Native American, 0 (0.0%) Asian, 0 (0.0%) Pacific Islander, 2 (1.9%) from other races, and 4 (3.8%) from two or more races.  Hispanic or Latino of any race were 11 people (10.4%).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.census.gov/2010census/popmap/ipmtext.php?fl=06:0623812|archive-url=https://archive.today/20140715024843/http://www.census.gov/2010census/popmap/ipmtext.php?fl=06:0623812|url-status=dead|archive-date=July 15, 2014|title=2010 Census Interactive Population Search: CA - Fellows CDP|publisher=U.S. Census Bureau|access-date=July 12, 2014}}</ref>

The whole population lived in households, no one lived in non-institutionalized group quarters and no one was institutionalized.

There were 37 households, 17 (45.9%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 25 (67.6%) were [[marriage|opposite-sex married couples]] living together, 6 (16.2%) had a female householder with no husband present, 1 (2.7%) had a male householder with no wife present.  There were 1 (2.7%) [[POSSLQ|unmarried opposite-sex partnerships]], and 0 (0%) [[same-sex partnerships|same-sex married couples or partnerships]]. 4 households (10.8%) were one person and 1 (2.7%) had someone living alone who was 65 or older. The average household size was 2.86.  There were 32 families (86.5% of households); the average family size was 3.06.

The age distribution was 29 people (27.4%) under the age of 18, 8 people (7.5%) aged 18 to 24, 19 people (17.9%) aged 25 to 44, 38 people (35.8%) aged 45 to 64, and 12 people (11.3%) who were 65 or older.  The median age was 40.0 years. For every 100 females, there were 116.3 males.  For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 102.6 males.

There were 40 housing units at an average density of 60.9 per square mile, of the occupied units 33 (89.2%) were owner-occupied and 4 (10.8%) were rented. The homeowner vacancy rate was 2.9%; the rental vacancy rate was 0%.  91 people (85.8% of the population) lived in owner-occupied housing units and 15 people (14.2%) lived in rental housing units.

